BEGIN:VCALENDAR
VERSION:2.0
PRODID:-//Volleyball Schedule Scraper//
NAME:Out Sports League
X-WR-CALNAME:Out Sports League
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Out Sports League] Wednesdays - Recreational (C/D)
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260708T182000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260708T210000
UID:Out_Sports_League-Wednesdays_-_Recreational_(C/D)-2026-07-08T18:20:00
DESCRIPTION:WEDNESDAY NIGHTS: RECREATIONAL LEAGUE\nWelcome to our new Wedn
 esday Night Recreational Indoor Volleyball League\, this is a Recreational
  league for players of the following skill levels:\n\nC – Lower Intermed
 iate. Improving players who inconsistently perform 3 hits and can't spike 
 with power.\nD – Novice / Beginner. Recreational players who are learnin
 g the rules and basic skills of the game.\n\nIf you're a competitive playe
 r please register for our Thursday or Friday night leagues. \n\nOUT Sport
 s League provides fun\, recreation\, and social sports league to Central F
 lorida's LGBTQ+ community. Our Indoor Volleyball league is designed to be 
 inclusive of people of skill levels and backgrounds. All of our leagues of
 fer a great opportunity to meet other people in our community in a fun\, f
 riendly\, and accepting atmosphere. Following the games we'll go to Distri
 ct Dive where you'll get a FREE DRINK ticket every week. This season is sp
 onsored by Pineapple Healthcare.\n\nCreate a TEAM! On Wednesdays you can b
 ecome a TEAM CAPTAIN and have your players register as TEAM PLAYERS. Pleas
 e note our leagues have a fixed capacity of 100 players\, if your team is 
 incomplete when registration closes or capacity is reached the league will
  add free agents to your team.\n\nDon't have a Team? Register as a FREE AG
 ENT and we will place you on a team. Free agents can also name a FRIEND(S)
  that they want to play with and the league will place you together.\n\n
 ❤️ 🧡 💛 💚 💙 💜🖤\n\nLEAGUE INFORMATION\n\n8 Week Indoor
  Volleyball Season\nWednesdays from July 8 - August 26\nMatches will start
  at 6:20\, 7:10 and 8:00pm\n\n- Players must be Beginner\, Novice or Lower
  Intermediate Skill Levels (C/D).\n- 12 Teams Maximum. Recreational Teams
  must have 9 players.\n- 6v6 matches with standard rotating rules\, no lib
 ero players and rally scoring.\n- Games are to 21 (win by 2 or first to 25
 ). Always play all 3 games.\n- All games are refereed. Each team is requir
 ed to contribute line judges.\n\nGames are played at:\nEnglewood Neighborh
 ood Center\n6123 La Costa Dr.\, Orlando\, FL 32807\n\nWeekly after parties
  at:\nDistrict Dive\n2401 E South St\, Orlando\, FL 32803\n\nREGISTRATION 
 INFORMATION\n\n$70 per Player\nLeague Fee Covers - T-Shirt\, Fields\, Equi
 pment\, Umpires\, Photos\, Awards\, and Weekly After Party!\n\nTEAM CAPTAI
 N* - Create a team of 9+ and invite your friends!\nTEAM PLAYER - Join an e
 xisting team (please only join if invited to a team)\nFREE AGENT - Don't h
 ave a team? No problem! Register without a team and you can list friends y
 ou want to play with. When league registration closes you will placed on a
  team.\n\nWant to play with a few friends?\nIf you have a buddy or a small
  group of friends who want to play together you can all register as Free A
 gents. During registration you will be prompted to list player(s) that you
 'd like to play with. Everyone should register separately and the league w
 ill then place you and your friends together on a team.\n\n* Please note t
 he league has a fixed capacity of 100 players\, if your team is incomplete
  when registration closes or capacity is reached the league will add free 
 agents to your team.\n\nFAQ\n\nI don't have a team\, can I still play?\nYe
 s\, register as an Individual and we will place you with a team.\n\nI will
  miss a few weeks\, can I still play?\nYes\, all teams have extra players 
 on them just in case you're absent on a given week. Teams can also use sub
 stitute players.\n\nHow do I make sure my friend and I play on the same te
 am?\nDuring registration there is a field where you can list the friend(s)
  you want to play with and the league will place you together.\n\nI don't 
 know how to play or don't think I'll be very good\, should I play?\nYes\, 
 join our Wednesday or Friday Night leagues aimed at new and developing pla
 yers and you will learn the basics in a fun\, encouraging environment.\n\
 nI'm not LGBTQ+\, can I still play?\nYes\, we are accepting to all people 
 as long as you consider yourself an ally to our community.\n\nMore info: h
 ttps://outsportsleague.leagueapps.com/leagues/volleyball-(indoor)/5048668-
 wednesdays---recreational-cd
LOCATION:Englewood Neighborhood Center
URL:https://outsportsleague.leagueapps.com/leagues/volleyball-(indoor)/504
 8668-wednesdays---recreational-cd
END:VEVENT
