BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Out Sports League] Thursdays - Competitive (A/B)
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260709T182000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260709T210000
UID:Out_Sports_League-Thursdays_-_Competitive_(A/B)-2026-07-09T18:20:00
DESCRIPTION:LEAGUE IS SOLD OUT! \nREGISTER TO JOIN THE WAIT LIST\n\nTHURS
 DAY NIGHTS: COMPETITIVE LEAGUE\nWelcome to our new Thursday Night Competit
 ive Indoor Volleyball League\, this is a Competitive league for players of
  the following skill levels:\n\nA – Advanced. Experienced and competitiv
 e players who execute plays consistently at a high level.\nB – Upper Int
 ermediate. Above average players who can bump\, set and spike consistently
 ..\n\nIf you're a recreational or beginning player please register for ou
 r Wednesday or Friday night leagues.\n\nOUT Sports League provides fun\, r
 ecreation\, and social sports league to Central Florida's LGBTQ+ community
 . Our Indoor Volleyball league is designed to be inclusive of people of sk
 ill levels and backgrounds. All of our leagues offer a great opportunity t
 o meet other people in our community in a fun\, friendly\, and accepting a
 tmosphere. Following the games we'll go to District Dive where you'll get 
 a FREE DRINK ticket every week. This season is sponsored by Pineapple Heal
 thcare.\n\nCreate a TEAM! On Thursdays you can become a TEAM CAPTAIN and h
 ave your players register as TEAM PLAYERS. Please note our leagues have a 
 fixed capacity of 96 players\, if your team is incomplete when registratio
 n closes or capacity is reached the league will add free agents to your te
 am.\n\nDon't have a Team? Register as a FREE AGENT and we will place you o
 n a team. Free agents can also name a FRIEND(S) that they want to play wit
 h and the league will place you together.\n\n❤️ 🧡 💛 💚 💙 
 💜🖤\n\nLEAGUE INFORMATION\n\n8 Week Indoor Volleyball Season\nThursda
 ys from July 9 - August 27\nMatches will start at 6:20\, 7:10 and 8:00pm\
 n\n- Players must be Advanced or Upper Intermediate Skill Levels (A/B).\n-
  12 Teams Maximum. Competitive Teams must have 8 players.\n- 6v6 matches w
 ith standard rotating rules\, no libero players and rally scoring.\n- Game
 s are to 21 (win by 2 or first to 25). Always play all 3 games.\n- All gam
 es are refereed. Each team is required to contribute line judges.\n\nGames
  are played at:\nDover Shores Neighborhood Center\n1400 Gaston Foster Rd\
 , Orlando\, FL 32812\n\nWeekly after parties at:\nDistrict Dive\n2401 E So
 uth St\, Orlando\, FL 32803\n\nREGISTRATION INFORMATION\n\n$70 per Player\
 nLeague Fee Covers - T-Shirt\, Fields\, Equipment\, Umpires\, Photos\, Awa
 rds\, and Weekly After Party!\n\nTEAM CAPTAIN* - Create a team of 8+ and i
 nvite your friends!\nTEAM PLAYER - Join an existing team (please only join
  if invited to a team)\nFREE AGENT - Don't have a team? No problem! Regist
 er without a team and you can list friends you want to play with. When lea
 gue registration closes you will placed on a team.\n\nWant to play with a 
 few friends?\nIf you have a buddy or a small group of friends who want to 
 play together you can all register as Free Agents. During registration you
  will be prompted to list player(s) that you'd like to play with. Everyone
  should register separately and the league will then place you and your fr
 iends together on a team.\n\n* Please note the league has a fixed capacity
  of 96 players\, if your team is incomplete when registration closes or ca
 pacity is reached the league will add free agents to your team.\n\nFAQ\n\n
 I don't have a team\, can I still play?\nYes\, register as an Individual a
 nd we will place you with a team.\n\nI will miss a few weeks\, can I still
  play?\nYes\, all teams have extra players on them just in case you're abs
 ent on a given week. Teams can also use substitute players.\n\nHow do I ma
 ke sure my friend and I play on the same team?\nDuring registration there 
 is a field where you can list the friend(s) you want to play with and the 
 league will place you together.\n\nI don't know how to play or don't think
  I'll be very good\, should I play?\nYes\, join our Wednesday or Friday Ni
 ght leagues aimed at new and developing players and you will learn the bas
 ics in a fun\, encouraging environment.\n\nI'm not LGBTQ+\, can I still pl
 ay?\nYes\, we are accepting to all people as long as you consider yourself
  an ally to our community.\n\nMore info: https://outsportsleague.leagueapp
 s.com/leagues/volleyball-(indoor)/5048669-thursdays---competitive-ab
LOCATION:Dover Shores Community Center
URL:https://outsportsleague.leagueapps.com/leagues/volleyball-(indoor)/504
 8669-thursdays---competitive-ab
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Out Sports League] Fridays - Draft/REMIX League (A/B/C/D)
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260710T182000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260710T210000
UID:Out_Sports_League-Fridays_-_Draft/REMIX_League_(A/B/C/D)-2026-07-10T18
 :20:00
DESCRIPTION:ONLY ACCEPTING PLAYERS INTO THE A/B (ADVANCED/UPPER INTERMEDI
 ATE) DIVISION\nIF YOU REGISTER AS A C/D PLAYER YOU WILL BE PLACED ON THE W
 AIT LIST AND REFUNDED\n\nFRIDAY NIGHTS: DRAFT/REMIX LEAGUE\nWelcome to our
  new Friday Night Draft Indoor Volleyball League\, this league will contai
 n 2 divisions containing of players of the following skill levels:\n\nCOMP
 ETITIVE DIVISION\nA – Advanced. Experienced and competitive players who 
 execute plays consistently at a high level.\nB – Upper Intermediate. Abo
 ve average players who can bump\, set and spike consistently.\n\nRECREATIO
 NAL DIVISION\nC – Lower Intermediate. Improving players who inconsistent
 ly perform 3 hits and can't spike with power.\nD – Novice / Beginner. Re
 creational players who are learning the rules and basic skills of the game
 .\n\nOUT Sports League provides fun\, recreation\, and social sports leagu
 e to Central Florida's LGBTQ+ community. Our Indoor Volleyball league is d
 esigned to be inclusive of people of skill levels and backgrounds. We offe
 r a Social Division (for beginners or players interested in a relaxed\, fu
 n atmosphere)\, and a Competitive Divisions (only players with prior indoo
 r volleyball experience who are secure in the rules are encouraged to play
  in the competitive division). All of our leagues offer a great opportunit
 y to meet other people in our community in a fun\, friendly\, and acceptin
 g atmosphere. Following the games we'll go to District Dive where you'll g
 et a FREE DRINK ticket every week.\n\nThis is a Draft/Remix League where a
 ll players register as an INDIVIDUAL. All players may name one (1) other p
 layer during registration that they'd like to be placed on a team with. Te
 ams will be created by a Captain's Draft or by the League.\n\n❤️ 🧡 
 💛 💚 💙 💜🖤\n\nLEAGUE INFORMATION\n\n8 Week Indoor Volleyball 
 Season\nFridays from July 10 - August 28\nCompetitive (A/B) and Recreation
 al (C/D) Divisions\nMatches will start at 6:20\, 7:10 and 8:00pm\n\n- 12 T
 eams Maximum with divisions determined by registration\n- Recreational Tea
 ms will have 9 players\, Competitive Teams will have 8 players.\n- 6v6 ma
 tches with standard rotating rules\, no libero players and rally scoring\n
 - Games are to 21 (win by 2 or first to 25). Always play all 3 games.\n- A
 ll games are refereed. Each team is required to contribute line judges.\n\
 nGames are played at:\nDover Shores Neighborhood Center\n1400 Gaston Foste
 r Rd\, Orlando\, FL 32812\n\nWeekly after parties at:\nDistrict Dive\n2401
  E South St\, Orlando\, FL 32803\n\nREGISTRATION INFORMATION\n\n$70 per Pl
 ayer\nLeague Fee Covers - T-Shirt\, Fields\, Equipment\, Umpires\, Photos\
 , Awards\, and Weekly After Party!\n\nINDIVIDUAL - All players register as
  an Individual. When league registration closes you will placed on a team
 .\n\nWant to play with a friend?\nIn a Draft/Remix Season players are perm
 itted to list one (1) other player that they'd like to be placed on a team
  with. Please make sure you and your friend list each other when prompted 
 during registration. Chains of friends are not permitted.\n\nFAQ\n\nI don
 't have a team\, can I still play?\nYes\, register as an Individual and we
  will place you with a team.\n\nI will miss a few weeks\, can I still play
 ?\nYes\, all teams have extra players on them just in case you're absent o
 n a given week. Teams can also use substitute players.\n\nHow do I make su
 re my friend and I play on the same team?\nDuring registration there is a 
 field where you can list the friend you want to play with and the league w
 ill place you together.\n\nI don't know how to play or don't think I'll be
  very good\, should I play?\nYes\, join our Wednesday or Friday Night leag
 ues aimed at new and developing players and you will learn the basics in a
  fun\, encouraging environment.\n\nI'm not LGBTQ+\, can I still play?\nYes
 \, we are accepting to all people as long as you consider yourself an ally
  to our community.\n\nMore info: https://outsportsleague.leagueapps.com/le
 agues/volleyball-(indoor)/5048670-fridays---draftremix-league-abcd
LOCATION:Dover Shores Community Center
URL:https://outsportsleague.leagueapps.com/leagues/volleyball-(indoor)/504
 8670-fridays---draftremix-league-abcd
END:VEVENT
