DESCRIPTION:ONLY ACCEPTING PLAYERS INTO THE A/B (ADVANCED/UPPER INTERMEDI
 ATE) DIVISION\nIF YOU REGISTER AS A C/D PLAYER YOU WILL BE PLACED ON THE W
 AIT LIST AND REFUNDED\n\nFRIDAY NIGHTS: DRAFT/REMIX LEAGUE\nWelcome to our
  new Friday Night Draft Indoor Volleyball League\, this league will contai
 n 2 divisions containing of players of the following skill levels:\n\nCOMP
 ETITIVE DIVISION\nA – Advanced. Experienced and competitive players who 
 execute plays consistently at a high level.\nB – Upper Intermediate. Abo
 ve average players who can bump\, set and spike consistently.\n\nRECREATIO
 NAL DIVISION\nC – Lower Intermediate. Improving players who inconsistent
 ly perform 3 hits and can't spike with power.\nD – Novice / Beginner. Re
 creational players who are learning the rules and basic skills of the game
 .\n\nOUT Sports League provides fun\, recreation\, and social sports leagu
 e to Central Florida's LGBTQ+ community. Our Indoor Volleyball league is d
 esigned to be inclusive of people of skill levels and backgrounds. We offe
 r a Social Division (for beginners or players interested in a relaxed\, fu
 n atmosphere)\, and a Competitive Divisions (only players with prior indoo
 r volleyball experience who are secure in the rules are encouraged to play
  in the competitive division). All of our leagues offer a great opportunit
 y to meet other people in our community in a fun\, friendly\, and acceptin
 g atmosphere. Following the games we'll go to District Dive where you'll g
 et a FREE DRINK ticket every week.\n\nThis is a Draft/Remix League where a
 ll players register as an INDIVIDUAL. All players may name one (1) other p
 layer during registration that they'd like to be placed on a team with. Te
 ams will be created by a Captain's Draft or by the League.\n\n❤️ 🧡 
 💛 💚 💙 💜🖤\n\nLEAGUE INFORMATION\n\n8 Week Indoor Volleyball 
 Season\nFridays from July 10 - August 28\nCompetitive (A/B) and Recreation
 al (C/D) Divisions\nMatches will start at 6:20\, 7:10 and 8:00pm\n\n- 12 T
 eams Maximum with divisions determined by registration\n- Recreational Tea
 ms will have 9 players\, Competitive Teams will have 8 players.\n- 6v6 ma
 tches with standard rotating rules\, no libero players and rally scoring\n
 - Games are to 21 (win by 2 or first to 25). Always play all 3 games.\n- A
 ll games are refereed. Each team is required to contribute line judges.\n\
 nGames are played at:\nDover Shores Neighborhood Center\n1400 Gaston Foste
 r Rd\, Orlando\, FL 32812\n\nWeekly after parties at:\nDistrict Dive\n2401
  E South St\, Orlando\, FL 32803\n\nREGISTRATION INFORMATION\n\n$70 per Pl
 ayer\nLeague Fee Covers - T-Shirt\, Fields\, Equipment\, Umpires\, Photos\
 , Awards\, and Weekly After Party!\n\nINDIVIDUAL - All players register as
  an Individual. When league registration closes you will placed on a team
 .\n\nWant to play with a friend?\nIn a Draft/Remix Season players are perm
 itted to list one (1) other player that they'd like to be placed on a team
  with. Please make sure you and your friend list each other when prompted 
 during registration. Chains of friends are not permitted.\n\nFAQ\n\nI don
 't have a team\, can I still play?\nYes\, register as an Individual and we
  will place you with a team.\n\nI will miss a few weeks\, can I still play
 ?\nYes\, all teams have extra players on them just in case you're absent o
 n a given week. Teams can also use substitute players.\n\nHow do I make su
 re my friend and I play on the same team?\nDuring registration there is a 
 field where you can list the friend you want to play with and the league w
 ill place you together.\n\nI don't know how to play or don't think I'll be
  very good\, should I play?\nYes\, join our Wednesday or Friday Night leag
 ues aimed at new and developing players and you will learn the basics in a
  fun\, encouraging environment.\n\nI'm not LGBTQ+\, can I still play?\nYes
 \, we are accepting to all people as long as you consider yourself an ally
  to our community.\n\nMore info: https://outsportsleague.leagueapps.com/le
